CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 24, 1952, pg. 13, reads: "DELTA JABBERWOCK - At A. Leo Weil School last Friday night the Delta Jabberwock was sparked by good singing, dancing and gay novelty acts. Helping to put the show over was this group of pretty chorines.  Among those pictured are Lyda Jo Boswell, Barbara Stout, Jackie Lewis, Lois Jean Dugan [Dougan], Mary Louise Brooks, Patricia Knott, Barbara Boswell, Barbara Goggins, Joan Davis, Judith Dehoney and Charmaine Jeffries.  Charmaine Jeffries was crowned 'Miss Jabberwock.' - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of thirteen young women from Delta sorority wearing satin dance costumes, front row from left: Lyda Jo Boswell, Barbara Stout, Jackie Lewis [Jacqui Thompson], Lois Jean Dougan in center, Lois Swope; also including Mary Louise Brooks, Patricia Knott, Barbara Boswell, Barbara Goggins, Jeanette Terry, Joan Davis, Judith Dehoney, Miss Jabberwock Charmaine Jeffries, and possibly Murdis Earl, posed in A. Leo Weil School
